<br>
Talisman Gate transports the caster to the Plane of Knowledge and requires &quot;Quintessence of Knowledge&quot; (stackable) as a reagent.  Quintessence of Knowledge can only be created by a Shaman's Alchemy and consumes 1 x Tanaan Ginko &amp; 1 x Erudition Vine (total cost, 105pp) to make it.<br>
<br>
So the end result?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>A gate potion that costs 300 mana to summon, has 1 charge, 30 second cast time, and requires a reagent costing 105pp that is obtained through Shaman Alchemy Only.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This is a joke, right?  A Shaman's Gate potion to Innothule will place the player within 60 seconds easy walking distance to a PoK portal book, IS STACKABLE (10 charges max), costs 168pp per charge (50pp more) but IS NOT NO RENT, takes one inventory slot (rather than 2 - Talisman and Reagent), and the player doesn't have to have a magician with the spell nearby to summon one for them!<br>
<br>
Remove the component from this spell and it would actually be a useful to the Magician class.  It would be an item that melees and hybrids would seek out at the beginning of a play session, just as they seek out <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3467&amp;source=Live" target="top">Virtue</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> now, or Casters seek out <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2570&amp;source=Live" target="top">Koadic's Endless Intellect</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  In it's current form it's useless, and we have enough useless summons already.<br>
<br>
Alternatively, remove the spell from the Magician line altogether, and add a new Shaman Alchemy potion that gates to PoK using the above recipe.  I'm sure the Shamans wouldn't mind, as to my knowledge Quintessence of Knowledge is the only Alchemy recipe that was added to the game with the PoP expansion anyway.<br>
<br>
Could you imagine the outcry if Wizards required a 50pp reagent made only via Rogue's Make Poison to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>summon</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> their familiar?  Why are we inflicted with such a restriction for our only teleportation spell.<br>
<br>
