<br>
For example, a Magician can hand out a Quintessence of Knowledge to each group member along with a Summoned: Talisman of Return, but they will be out of pocket 105pp for each time they do this.  Star Rubies are still very expensive (approx. 70pp) and are not carried by very many Magicians as they are only for one rare circumstantial spell.<br>
<br>
Why then would you take a Magician anywhere you would need a way out of later, when a Druid or Wizard can do the same for free (or translocate for 1.1pp, a cost easily carried by the Wizard personally or reclaimed from the group's loot).<br>
<br>
Remember, the Talisman is a 30 second gate.  A Wizard or Druid is still exceptional in areas where there is need of much faster transport, group transport, or the need to transport to anywhere other than the Plane of Knowledge (Cobalt Scar for example).  The Magician's Talisman certainly doesn't replace this ability.<br>
<br>
The Magician's Talisman is only a convenient way out of a safe area (30 seconds can be a long time in a dangerous place) to a place where you can camp, or continue your travels.<br>
<br>
I would agree with with the spell using a pearl as a reagent.  The pearls are appox. 5pp, virtually guaranteed to be carried in stacks by any 56  Magician.  Additionally, they are already used as a reagent for the existing Magician &quot;teleport spell&quot; (CotH) and thus seem to fit very well with the Talisman idea. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365" target="top">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=279732" target="top">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=promethiuz>Promethiuz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 11:01:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=163.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Talisman of Return - Remove the reagent please.</span><hr size=1> When I first heard of this spell I thouught it would eb great. I'm bound in PoM and that is a major hassle for traveling. Then I find out it has a reagent, it's usefullness was cut by half. Then I find out the reagent is shamen made only AND cost 100pp PER ATTEMPT. The usefullness has been removed completely. Right now I am 63 with 2 scrolls of Talismon in the bank, none in my spell book. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=228778">Promethiuz 63 Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
